st will auto-scan. This is a STALENESS DETECTOR not a scanner — makes staleness VISIBLE. VERIFICATION: Proptest: trace_check returns stale iff any file mtime > stored mtime. Unit test: modify file → stale. Run scan → fresh. IMPORTANT: mtime check goes in CLI layer (IO), not kernel (pure). DEPENDS-ON: T7-1 (auto-trace on harvest) already done. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-002 (CC-2 impl satisfies spec), INV-WITNESS-011.; PROPOSAL-6: Comprehensive Trace Scan at Session Start. PROBLEM: 115 spec-impl gaps are mostly false positives because trace scanning only runs at harvest. Many spec elements have tests referencing them that haven't been scanned. SOLUTION: Run braid trace scan --incremental at session start. Incremental mode: only scan files with mtime > last-scan-mtime. Cost: ~0.5s for changed files only. This closes the false-positive gaps and makes F(S) accurate. VERIFICATION: Before: 115 gaps. After comprehensive scan: gaps should drop by 30-50%. Incremental scan takes < 1s. DEPENDS-ON: Proposal 3 (staleness detector provides the mtime infrastructure). TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-HARVEST-001.; PROPOSAL-1: Task Audit ACP Conversion. PROBLEM: braid task audit generates per-task evidence (confidence%, spec coverage, file paths) but output is truncated by apply_budget_gate because task audit isn't ACP-converted. It uses CommandOutput::from_human() with no _acp field, so maybe_inject_footer applies legacy truncation. SOLUTION: Convert task audit to ACP. Action = close command (never truncated). Context = per-task evidence blocks at UserRequested precedence. Evidence pointer = 'braid task show t-xxx'. Same pattern as task ready/show/close. VERIFICATION: Test that audit output in agent mode contains close command AND at least one evidence block. Proptest: audit Action is non-empty for any store with auditable tasks. DEPENDS-ON: None (standalone). TRACES TO: INV-BUDGET-007 (ACP Completeness), INV-INTERFACE-001.; PROPOSAL-4: Session Delta Display for F(S). PROBLEM: F(S) 